1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:13,719
I'm Jinla. From <i>The Contenic.</i>

2
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:15,359
Do I need to introduce myself?

3
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:17,759
Do you know
why I keep looking for ways to die?

4
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:22,239
Aren't you worried Mr. Chan would be sad
if something happened to you?

5
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:25,760
I think he'd be
the happiest one if I died.

6
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:29,400
Ms. Claire's helicopter crashed.

7
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:35,200
<i>Am I Ms. Claire?</i>

8
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:37,400
<i>Am I Ms. Claire?</i>

9
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:51,279
Claire. Claire. Claire.

10
00:00:51,280 --> 00:00:52,360
Claire.

11
00:00:52,880 --> 00:00:55,079
Hey, Claire, stay still.

12
00:00:55,080 --> 00:00:57,560
The more you move, the more it'll hurt.

13
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:04,599
Let go. Let me go. Hey, let go.

14
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:07,400
Hey, let me go.

15
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,559
Claire.

16
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:13,800
Don't wander off like that again.

17
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:15,920
I'll get you some water.

18
00:01:25,160 --> 00:01:26,920
Do you want to ask me questions,

19
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:30,040
or should I tell you

20
00:01:31,080 --> 00:01:32,440
what happened to you?

21
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,760
I'm not Ms. Claire.

22
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:49,879
I...

23
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:52,559
I don't know how to explain it.

24
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:56,800
My face and my voice are Ms. Claire's,
but I'm really not her.

25
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,199
Then who are you?

26
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,040
I'm Jinla.

27
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:19,160
Claire.

28
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:29,400
Claire.

29
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,640
I'm not Nitchan, your fiancé, either.

30
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,040
I'm Chan's friend

31
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:42,680
who's lived in his body
since our car accident as kids.

32
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,160
That's what I thought...

33
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,040
after I woke up.

34
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,000
My friend and I

35
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,840
went out for a drive.

36
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,280
Then we had an accident.

37
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,640
When I woke up,

38
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,560
I thought I was my friend
who died in the accident.

39
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:36,519
What you're going through
right now, Claire,

40
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,960
comes from shock.

41
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,280
You were in severe shock

42
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:43,920
before the crash.

43
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:50,520
The last thing you saw...

44
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,360
was a woman called Jinla.

45
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:03,480
<i>So now that you're awake,</i>

46
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,760
you think you're her.

47
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:17,119
No. That's not it. I'm not imagining this.

48
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,279
I'm really not Ms. Claire.

49
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,760
I need you to be patient, Claire.

50
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:28,560
The doctor said you'll get better.

51
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,720
And you'll become yourself again.

52
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:35,120
- Hey.
- Claire.

53
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:38,480
Let's not talk about this right now.

54
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:41,080
I want you to rest.

55
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:48,520
We can discuss it when we get home.

56
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:56,040
Hey, hey, don't go. Wait. Hear me out.

57
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:59,760
You've got it wrong.
I'm really not Ms. Claire.

58
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,880
I'm Jinla.

59
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:15,120
You have to believe me.
I'm telling the truth.

60
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,040
Claire.

61
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:24,120
Remember what I told you?

62
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:27,640
If you won't behave
and keep making a scene,

63
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:32,080
you'll be given a sedative again.

64
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,000
Do you want that?

65
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,600
Help!

66
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:51,880
Is anyone out there?!

67
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:53,679
Help!

68
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:56,280
Is anyone out there?! Help...

69
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,240
Ms. Claire.

70
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,560
Who are you?

71
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,400
I'm Tunlathon.

72
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:17,880
Tunlathon?

73
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,439
Hello, I'm Tunlathon.

74
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:24,840
- I run Ms. Claire's security team.
- Okay.

75
00:08:26,440 --> 00:08:28,240
Do you need anything, Ms. Claire?

76
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,240
Open the door.

77
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:34,600
I'm sorry, but I can't do that.

78
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:41,840
Can you at least tell me where I am?

79
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:44,720
Mr. Chan will tell you everything himself.

80
00:08:45,520 --> 00:08:47,960
My duty is to keep you safe.

81
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:30,560
<i>Claire. You're Claire, not Jinla.</i>

82
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,760
I'm Jinla.

83
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,920
I'm Jinla.

84
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,320
I really am Jinla.

85
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,960
The food is ready.

86
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:24,880
Would you like to eat here?
I'll tell the staff to bring it over.

87
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:26,840
Go ahead and eat.

88
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:30,040
I want to sit here for a while.

89
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,360
Dad, Mom.

90
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,559
You're both here.

91
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,880
Can I discuss something with you, Dad?

92
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,799
Here, Dad.

93
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,639
It's for TGL's 60th anniversary event.

94
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:47,919
I want to set up booths at the venue
to promote our older projects.

95
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:50,680
We'll offer a 60% discount
to match the event theme.

96
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:53,800
It would help
clear out our older projects.

97
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,520
Sounds good.

98
00:10:57,640 --> 00:11:00,480
I heard you also
want to issue corporate bonds.

99
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:02,440
Yes.

100
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:05,479
I want to issue corporate bonds too, Dad,

101
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,999
with a 6% interest rate,

102
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,479
to match the 60th anniversary theme.

103
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:13,400
We might raise at least
five billion baht from this event.

104
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,240
Postpone it.

105
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,440
Postpone it?

106
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,280
Dad,

107
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:30,079
I understand
you're postponing it to wait for Claire.

108
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,840
But what if she doesn't come back?

109
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,920
Cha.

110
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:36,680
Don't upset your dad like that.

111
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:38,959
But I'm telling the truth, Mom.

112
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,199
Or should I say it outright?

113
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,879
Waiting for her is pointless.

114
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:45,559
We don't even know
if Claire survived the crash.

115
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:47,440
- Is that better?
- That's enough!

116
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:50,720
Do whatever you want!

117
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:56,279
Cha, Cha.

118
00:11:56,280 --> 00:11:58,759
Dad, I'm not trying to curse Claire.

119
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,719
But waiting around like this
has already cost us projects.

120
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:04,359
And we're losing money
over something hopeless.

121
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,719
Enough!

122
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:07,919
Rin, tell your daughter to shut up

123
00:12:07,920 --> 00:12:10,400
before I get even angrier.

124
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,080
Cha.

125
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:14,079
That's enough.

126
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:16,759
But it's true. You keep believing Chan

127
00:12:16,760 --> 00:12:18,399
that Claire is recovering.

128
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,439
If she's better,

129
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:22,959
why hasn't he taken you to her
to see for yourself she's not dead?

130
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:23,920
Cha.

131
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,680
It's for Claire's safety.

132
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,600
Chan.

133
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,600
How is Claire?

134
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,519
All good, sir.

135
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,079
All good?

136
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:41,559
That's all you ever tell him.

137
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:45,360
Can you elaborate
on what you mean by "all good"?

138
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,399
Chan.

139
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:53,080
Our people at TGL said Ms. Cha's
called an executive meeting tomorrow.

140
00:12:57,080 --> 00:13:00,360
Then I should go tell
her father the good news about Claire.

141
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:03,080
Please take care of Claire.

142
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:04,760
You got it.

143
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:11,760
It means Claire is now...

144
00:13:17,240 --> 00:13:18,680
awake, sir.

145
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:25,920
Then...

146
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:29,559
When can I see her?

147
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:32,079
It will take a little more time.

148
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,799
Claire has woken up,

149
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:37,280
but she was unconscious for many months.

150
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:43,600
She'll need physical therapy for a while
before she can move normally again.

151
00:13:50,320 --> 00:13:51,880
What is so funny?

152
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,559
It is funny, Dad.

153
00:13:54,560 --> 00:13:56,400
I'm laughing at his excuses.

154
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,959
You say Claire is better and recovering.

155
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:03,279
Then why haven't you taken him,
so he can see for himself?

156
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:04,440
That's not it.

157
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:08,079
Chan told me he would let me see her

158
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:11,560
when she has recovered
as much as possible.

159
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:14,800
I've waited six months.

160
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,800
What's wrong with waiting a little longer?

161
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,480
Don't disappoint me.

162
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:29,400
I won't, sir.

163
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,440
Ms. Claire?

164
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:58,840
The doctor says
you can have soft foods now.

165
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:02,800
Would you prefer congee or pumpkin soup?

166
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,560
Ms. Claire?

167
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,240
I'm coming in.

168
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:21,560
Ms. Claire?

169
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:31,440
Ms. Claire?

170
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:39,880
Ms. Claire.

171
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:43,080
Ms. Claire?

172
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:46,920
Ms. Claire?

173
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,400
Is he asleep?

174
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:13,200
No.

175
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:16,319
He's reading.

176
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:19,600
Is there something
you two want to discuss with me?

177
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:24,120
You know
what will happen if you lie, right?

178
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,400
Is Claire really awake?

179
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:31,160
Then why haven't you brought her back?

180
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,399
Well...

181
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:39,039
As I told your father, Claire is awake.

182
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,679
But she's not very strong yet.

183
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:43,040
Don't worry.

184
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:47,440
I will definitely
bring her back to her own home.

185
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,560
Besides,

186
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:53,359
the reason I haven't brought her back

187
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:55,880
is for her own safety.

188
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,280
For her safety?

189
00:17:00,560 --> 00:17:02,880
Or for your own safety?

190
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:06,598
Because if Claire dies,

191
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:10,159
your status as her fiancé ends,

192
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:12,960
and you'll go back
to being Dad's driver's son.

193
00:17:22,800 --> 00:17:24,400
I think you misunderstand.

194
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:29,480
Even now, I'm still the driver's son.

195
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:31,999
In fact,

196
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:35,600
you and I aren't that different.

197
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,880
If there's nothing else, please excuse me.

198
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,120
Don't worry.

199
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:56,560
I will definitely
bring her back to her own home.

200
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,280
What's up, Tun?

201
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:22,520
What? Claire ran away?

202
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,600
Yes. I'm sorry.

203
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,680
I'm looking for her.
She can't have gone far.

204
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,920
Okay, I'll hurry back.

205
00:19:11,720 --> 00:19:12,680
Miss!

206
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,160
Miss!

207
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,120
Miss!

208
00:19:29,120 --> 00:19:30,800
Come out! Don't run!

209
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,600
Miss!

210
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:39,400
Miss!

211
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,800
Miss!

212
00:21:35,240 --> 00:21:37,520
Help.

213
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,119
Help me.

214
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:41,520
Please help me. Help.

215
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,720
Hello, miss.

216
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,439
Are you okay? What happened?

217
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,359
Help... help me, please.

218
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:58,119
Alright, please calm down.

219
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,079
- This way.
- Get in, miss.

220
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:01,800
- Help...
- This way, please.

221
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:08,000
Alright, don't worry. You're safe now.

222
00:22:09,760 --> 00:22:10,760
There you go.

223
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:37,679
Officers.

224
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,559
Officers, please stop.

225
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,159
Stop the car.

226
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,480
Officers.

227
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,599
I'm not Ms. Claire.

228
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:49,840
Officers, you have to
take me away from here. Officers.

229
00:22:57,480 --> 00:23:00,160
Officers. Officers. Officers!

230
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,880
Hello.

231
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:12,080
We found Ms. Claire running on the road.

232
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:13,759
Thank you, Captain.

233
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:14,800
Sure.

234
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:31,320
Get out.

235
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:37,720
Are you surprised?

236
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:43,440
I asked the captain to help
with the security of this house

237
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:46,280
from the first day you moved in.

238
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,080
Get out.

239
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,760
Get out, or I'll carry you out.

240
00:24:05,440 --> 00:24:08,600
Hey, hey. Let go. Let go of me.

241
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:10,639
Let go.

242
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:13,199
Officer, help me. Please help me.

243
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:15,479
Officer. Officer!

244
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:18,359
Officer, take me away from here. Officer!

245
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:19,759
Thank you very much, Officer.

246
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,239
Drive safely.

247
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,479
- Of course. Excuse me.
- Hey!

248
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,920
I told you to let go. Let go.

249
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:27,399
I'm not going.

250
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:29,279
Let go. Let go of me.

251
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,639
I said let go.

252
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,159
Let go.

253
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:33,479
Hey, let go.

254
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,720
Let me go.

255
00:24:38,800 --> 00:24:39,919
Tell me honestly.

256
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,120
Why are you so desperate to escape?

257
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:45,999
You don't believe me
that I'm Jinla, not Ms. Claire.

258
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:48,159
And don't you dare tell me

259
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:50,879
I'm in shock and my memories got mixed up.

260
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:55,040
If I really were her,
I would have her memories.

261
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:59,480
But the only memories I have
tell me I'm Jinla.

262
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,920
The woman called Jinla...

263
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,640
is 30 years old.

264
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:12,400
She was born on January 7.

265
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,999
When she was five,

266
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:19,160
she was in a car accident
and lost both her parents.

267
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:23,719
After that, her aunt, Nalin, took her in.

268
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:27,120
And she's lived with her aunt ever since.

269
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,120
You're wondering
how I know that, aren't you?

270
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:36,000
You told me to look into her.

271
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,040
What?

272
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:44,919
Do you think a woman
like Khaedarun Kanchathara

273
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:48,440
would let just anyone interview her
without knowing who they are?

274
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,559
You may still be in shock right now,

275
00:25:51,560 --> 00:25:54,679
but you told me to look into her.

276
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,760
And that information is what confused you

277
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,960
and made you think you're her.

278
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:06,919
No, no. That's not true.

279
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:08,599
I'm not Ms. Claire.

280
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,200
Hey.

281
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,080
Stop thinking you're someone else.

282
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:17,439
You are Khaedarun Kanchathara,

283
00:26:17,440 --> 00:26:20,319
a woman everyone
in this world wants to be.

284
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:22,999
No! I told you I'm not Ms. Claire. Let go!

285
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,599
I said I'm not her!

286
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:25,800
Hey!

287
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:27,680
What are you doing?

288
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:29,560
I'm not Ms. Claire!

289
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:32,039
Claire, what are you doing?

290
00:26:32,040 --> 00:26:33,359
Stop calling me Ms. Claire.

291
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:35,560
I told you I'm not her!

292
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,759
But you really are Ms. Claire.

293
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:41,479
No! I know who I am.

294
00:26:41,480 --> 00:26:43,400
I remember myself as a child.

295
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:46,040
I remember Aunt Lin.

296
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,319
Think about it.

297
00:26:48,320 --> 00:26:50,839
Wouldn't you know who you are?

298
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,759
But you really are Ms. Claire.

299
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:53,999
Please calm down.

300
00:26:54,000 --> 00:26:57,560
I'm Jinla. I'm not Ms. Claire!

301
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:03,520
I'm not Ms. Claire. I'm Jinla.
Do you hear me?

302
00:27:04,120 --> 00:27:05,399
This isn't me!

303
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:08,520
This isn't my face. Do you understand?

304
00:27:09,720 --> 00:27:11,600
- Give me the knife.
- No.

305
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:13,959
Don't come near me.

306
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,080
Ms. Claire.

307
00:27:16,360 --> 00:27:19,400
I'm not Ms. Claire. I told you I'm Jinla.

308
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:22,280
Why won't you guys believe me?

309
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:27,280
This isn't my face. This isn't my face.

310
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:32,000
Don't come near me.

311
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:39,600
This isn't me. Do you understand?

312
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,680
This is not me.

313
00:27:44,600 --> 00:27:46,360
No, no, no, no, no!

314
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,040
Okay.

315
00:27:49,760 --> 00:27:51,040
You're right.

316
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:55,600
You're not Claire.

317
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:00,760
You're Jinla.

318
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:09,400
Chan.

319
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,520
Then...

320
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,680
what happened to me?

321
00:28:23,920 --> 00:28:26,160
Why did I become Ms. Claire?

322
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:28,640
You're not Claire.

323
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,720
We just made you look like her.

324
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:35,680
Why?

325
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:39,799
Why did you make me look like her?

326
00:28:39,800 --> 00:28:42,280
Why? And where is she?

327
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:46,640
Where is Ms. Claire?

328
00:28:58,360 --> 00:28:59,400
She's dead.

329
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:16,440
My goodness! Hurry! Quick!

330
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:27,920
Ms. Claire...

331
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,360
Ms. Claire really is dead?

332
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:52,800
Then what happened to me?

333
00:29:53,840 --> 00:29:56,439
What happened to me?
Why do I have Ms. Claire's face?

334
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:59,479
I think we should talk about this later.

335
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:02,599
For now, just know who you are.

336
00:30:02,600 --> 00:30:06,519
No! Tell me right now why I became her!

337
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:08,759
Why is this my face now?

338
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:12,360
- Tell me!
- Hey, hey. Hey, calm down.

339
00:30:12,960 --> 00:30:14,239
We had a reason.

340
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,559
A reason?

341
00:30:15,560 --> 00:30:18,279
I don't care what reason you had.

342
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:20,640
You had no right to do this to me!

343
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:25,320
You want to know why I did this, right?

344
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,240
Did Claire ever tell you
about her grandfather?

345
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:32,279
He's the chairman of TGL Group.

346
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:34,200
And he has heart disease.

347
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,240
I was afraid...

348
00:30:38,320 --> 00:30:40,959
if he found out
what really happened to her,

349
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:43,800
his heart would give out
and it would kill him.

350
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,160
What?

351
00:30:48,120 --> 00:30:50,960
You were worried
her grandfather would die,

352
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:54,800
so you decided to let me die instead?

353
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,799
Why?! Why?!

354
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:59,199
Why would you do this?!

355
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:02,639
Are you all out of your minds?!
How could you do this to me?!

356
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:03,919
Hey!

357
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:06,079
How could you do this to me?

358
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:07,319
Get the sleeping pills.

359
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,759
How could you do this to me?!

360
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:11,200
Will you calm down?

361
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:13,560
You're all insane.

362
00:31:23,880 --> 00:31:25,160
<i>Where are you now?</i>

363
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:29,120
Okay, I'll hurry back.

364
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:44,560
Chan is heading out.
Follow him and report back to me.

365
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,240
Hey, where are you going?

366
00:31:50,040 --> 00:31:52,799
To see with my own eyes
if Claire is really dead.

367
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:56,679
And then what? Are you following him
just to see if he's lying?

368
00:31:56,680 --> 00:32:00,039
Mom, if Claire is really dead,
that's a good thing.

369
00:32:00,040 --> 00:32:01,800
But what if she's not?

370
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:04,319
I'm gonna make sure

371
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:06,840
that she won't
set foot in that house again.

372
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:16,879
Help! Help me! Help!

373
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:19,080
- Be quiet. Quiet.
- Help me!

374
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:23,880
If you don't want me
to kill you right now, be quiet.

375
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:25,840
Tun, check who's here.

376
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:27,680
Okay.

377
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,240
I said be quiet.

378
00:32:43,200 --> 00:32:44,120
Ms. Cha?

379
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:55,800
Quiet. I said be quiet. Quiet.

380
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:11,600
Ms. Cha.

381
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:15,639
What? Why are you so shocked to see me?

382
00:33:15,640 --> 00:33:17,000
Of course I am.

383
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:20,680
I didn't expect you to
come here so late at night.

384
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:22,280
Why are you here?

385
00:33:22,880 --> 00:33:25,480
What about you? Why are you here?

386
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,480
I watch the house for Mr. Chan.

387
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,640
I'll let you go,

388
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,999
but you have to
promise me you'll stay quiet.

389
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:35,000
Can you do that?

390
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:41,839
Really?

391
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:43,080
Ms. Cha.

392
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:45,160
What are you doing?

393
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,719
My father hired you to watch Claire.

394
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:49,679
If you're here, she's here.

395
00:33:49,680 --> 00:33:51,239
- Move.
- Ms. Cha.

396
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:52,399
Ms. Cha.

397
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:54,400
What are you doing, Ms. Cha?

398
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:59,120
Where exactly is your boss?

399
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:02,599
- Mr. Chan's in his office.
- I don't mean Chan.

400
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,359
I mean Claire.

401
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:05,720
She's here, isn't she?

402
00:34:06,400 --> 00:34:07,960
I'm not at liberty to say.

403
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:10,920
I think you should leave.

404
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:14,960
If the chairman finds out you showed
up here, you could get in trouble.

405
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:18,760
How dare you threaten me?

406
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,840
The only thing that will make me leave

407
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:24,919
is seeing with my own eyes
whether Claire is alive or dead.

408
00:34:24,920 --> 00:34:25,840
Got that?!

409
00:34:26,760 --> 00:34:29,280
Ms. Cha. Ms. Cha.

410
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:31,320
Ms. Cha.

411
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:34,718
Ms. Cha. Ms. Cha.

412
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:35,840
Move.

413
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,880
Ms. Cha.

414
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,120
Ms. Cha.

415
00:34:42,040 --> 00:34:43,120
Ms. Cha.

416
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:50,719
Stay here. Don't go anywhere.

417
00:34:51,600 --> 00:34:53,239
For your own safety.

418
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,199
Do you understand?

419
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:57,240
Do you understand?

420
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:11,840
Ms. Cha.

421
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:14,960
Ms. Cha.

422
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:19,280
How dare you touch me? Let go.

423
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:21,520
I'm sorry.

424
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:24,800
But I can't let you do
whatever you want here.

425
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:27,920
Let go! Let go!

426
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:30,160
It's okay, Tun.

427
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:40,640
Do you think Ms. Claire is here?

428
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:43,399
You said Claire woke up.

429
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:46,080
So I wanted to be the first to greet her.

430
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:57,520
If I tell you the truth,

431
00:35:58,800 --> 00:36:02,640
can you promise me
that you won't tell the chairman?

432
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:06,600
- What truth?
- Promise me first.

433
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:09,880
Because what I'm about to tell you

434
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:13,040
could make the chairman's condition worse.

435
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,080
Chan.

436
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,520
Fine. What truth?

437
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:41,640
Ms. Claire...

438
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:53,920
Ms. Claire is dead.

439
00:36:58,080 --> 00:37:01,880
Ms. Claire died
on the day of the helicopter crash.

440
00:37:02,840 --> 00:37:04,640
But I didn't tell the chairman

441
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:08,320
because I was worried he couldn't take it.

442
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:20,040
Are you telling the truth?

443
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,640
Yes.

444
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:29,240
Ms. Cha. Ms. Cha.

445
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:30,960
Ms. Cha.

446
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,600
Ms. Cha.

447
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,799
<i>This isn't me!</i>

448
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:52,080
<i>I'm not Ms. Claire. Do you understand?</i>

449
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,880
You're not Claire.

450
00:38:55,680 --> 00:38:57,040
You're Jinla.

451
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,520
<i>What happened to me?</i>

452
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:04,839
<i>What happened to me?
Why do I have Ms. Claire's face?</i>

453
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:06,199
<i>You're not Claire.</i>

454
00:39:06,200 --> 00:39:08,400
<i>We just made you look like Claire.</i>

455
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:12,999
<i>Her grandfather is
the chairman of TGL Group.</i>

456
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:14,600
<i>And he has heart disease.</i>

457
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:17,799
<i>If he found out
what really happened to Claire,</i>

458
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:20,239
his heart would give out
and it would kill him.

459
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:22,880
You were worried
her grandfather would die,

460
00:39:23,400 --> 00:39:25,680
so you decided to let me die instead?

461
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,600
No, this isn't happening.

462
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,320
I'm not Claire.

463
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:34,040
I'm not Claire.

464
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:37,320
I'm not Claire. I'm not Claire.

465
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:58,160
Do you still have any doubts?
You can go back in and check again.

466
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:04,920
You know how serious it is
that you lied about Claire, right?

467
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:07,880
I do.

468
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:10,200
And I have no excuse.

469
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:12,759
I only ask one thing.

470
00:40:12,760 --> 00:40:15,800
Keep your promise
and don't tell the chairman.

471
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:40,800
Tun, we need to find her
as soon as possible.

472
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:43,759
If she tells anyone
we turned her into Claire,

473
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:46,240
everything we've planned will be in vain.

474
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,080
Then let's split up.

475
00:40:50,240 --> 00:40:51,280
Let's go.

476
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:47,160
Wait! Help me!

477
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:50,280
Wait! Help!

478
00:41:54,200 --> 00:41:56,800
Wait! Help me! Over here!

479
00:41:58,080 --> 00:41:59,280
Wait!

480
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:04,360
Wait for me!

481
00:42:08,360 --> 00:42:09,560
Over here!

482
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:17,160
Help!

483
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:20,040
Help! Don't!

484
00:42:36,040 --> 00:42:37,080
Miss.

485
00:42:38,520 --> 00:42:39,840
Miss.

486
00:42:40,560 --> 00:42:42,639
- Miss.
- What the hell? Do you want to die?

487
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:47,279
Please help me. Let me ride with you.

488
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,479
I'm not a robber. I've been attacked.

489
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:51,559
Please let me ride with you.

490
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:52,919
I can sit in the back.

491
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,960
Please drop me off just up ahead.

492
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:57,319
Please, I'm begging you.

493
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,600
Go on then.

494
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:00,040
Sit in the back.

495
00:43:00,960 --> 00:43:02,119
Come on, get in the back.

496
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,239
In the back, okay?

497
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:05,920
Yes. Thank you. Thank you so much.

498
00:44:03,040 --> 00:44:05,000
Tun. No luck?

499
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:06,760
No.

500
00:44:09,600 --> 00:44:10,759
Chan.

501
00:44:10,760 --> 00:44:12,800
I'm sorry I let her get away.

502
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:14,599
It's okay.

503
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:18,680
It's my fault for telling her the truth.
She lost it and ran away.

504
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,519
So...

505
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:25,360
why did you tell her
the truth that she's not Claire?

506
00:44:26,240 --> 00:44:29,999
If we don't tell her the truth now
and she finds out later

507
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:33,000
and loses it in front
of the chairman, it'll be even worse.

508
00:44:37,440 --> 00:44:38,440
Chan.

509
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:42,879
Are you sure you want to do this?

510
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:47,319
I'm asking you again because
once we take her to meet the chairman,

511
00:44:47,320 --> 00:44:50,240
there will be no turning back.

512
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:10,280
Tun.

513
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:12,920
Tell the press...

514
00:45:13,880 --> 00:45:15,279
Claire is the survivor.

515
00:45:15,280 --> 00:45:17,639
As for the details of her treatment,

516
00:45:17,640 --> 00:45:19,360
we'll keep them confidential.

517
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:22,320
Okay.

518
00:45:23,480 --> 00:45:25,960
And what should I tell Ms. Jinla's family?

519
00:45:27,600 --> 00:45:29,480
Tell them she died at the scene.

520
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:33,040
What?

521
00:45:35,880 --> 00:45:37,719
We'll take responsibility.

522
00:45:37,720 --> 00:45:39,440
Compensation and funeral expenses.

523
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:42,959
Find out how much she makes per month.

524
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:43,879
Chan.

525
00:45:43,880 --> 00:45:45,320
Then calculate...

526
00:45:46,120 --> 00:45:49,759
how much
she would earn if she lived to 80.

527
00:45:49,760 --> 00:45:50,839
What are you trying to do?

528
00:45:50,840 --> 00:45:52,879
She's still alive. She's not dead.

529
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:54,640
How can we say she's dead?

530
00:46:02,840 --> 00:46:04,200
We'll make her Claire.

531
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:07,560
What?

532
00:46:10,640 --> 00:46:11,680
Tun.

533
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:16,040
You know how fragile
the chairman's heart is.

534
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:18,640
If he finds out Claire's dead,

535
00:46:19,280 --> 00:46:21,439
imagine what would happen.

536
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:24,440
The only way to put everything back

537
00:46:25,640 --> 00:46:27,760
is to make the woman called Jinla

538
00:46:28,360 --> 00:46:29,520
become Claire.

539
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:37,679
I've been sure since I made that decision.

540
00:46:37,680 --> 00:46:40,040
And I'll never turn back.

541
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:43,999
Actually, if Ms. Cha hadn't shown up,

542
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,959
I'm sure we could've made Jinla

543
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:48,920
go along with our plan.

544
00:46:49,520 --> 00:46:53,840
Do you think Ms. Cha will keep
her promise not to tell the chairman?

545
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,040
No way.

546
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:58,880
She'll definitely tell him.

547
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:01,760
So I said what she wanted to hear most.

548
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:03,439
Think about it.

549
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:06,759
If she'd opened the door
and found Jinla in the room,

550
00:47:06,760 --> 00:47:09,599
Jinla would've told her
what we did to her.

551
00:47:09,600 --> 00:47:14,039
And if Ms. Cha
told the chairman, wouldn't he...

552
00:47:14,040 --> 00:47:15,800
We can't ever let him find out.

553
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:24,280
And where do you think she could've gone?

554
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:28,680
I have no idea. Here's the plan.

555
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:31,240
I'll look for Jinla myself.

556
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:34,639
In the meantime,
keep an eye on the chairman.

557
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:37,080
Don't let Ms. Cha tell him about this.

558
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:57,440
Lin is dead too.

559
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:00,319
Because of you.

560
00:48:00,320 --> 00:48:02,639
If you hadn't
locked me up in the hospital,

561
00:48:02,640 --> 00:48:04,799
my aunt wouldn't have died.

562
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:06,800
Because I need you to be Claire.

563
00:48:07,320 --> 00:48:08,880
What if I refuse?

564
00:48:09,400 --> 00:48:10,960
What if I refuse to be her?

565
00:48:11,720 --> 00:48:14,119
Is Chan really bringing Claire back?

566
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:17,720
What if everything he said is a lie?
